[{"Timecode":"","Caption":"{QTtext}{timescale:100}{font:Verdana}{size:20}{backColor:0,0,0}\r\n{textColor:65280,65280,65280}{width:960}{justify:center}\r\n{plain}\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:00.00]","Caption":"- [Voiceover] Hi there,\r\nmy name is Ron Friedman\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:03.01]","Caption":"and welcome to Rigging a\r\nHumanoid Character in Blender.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:06.00]","Caption":"Blender is a very powerful 3D modeling,\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:08.01]","Caption":"animation and rendering application.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:10.01]","Caption":"It can be used to create visuals\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:11.06]","Caption":"for animations, special\r\neffects, and gaming.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:14.01]","Caption":"Probably one of the best\r\nthings about Blender\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:16.01]","Caption":"is that it's free.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:17.02]","Caption":"It's an Open Source application\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:18.08]","Caption":"so you can download it whenever you want\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:20.04]","Caption":"and use it on OS X, Windows, or Linux.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:23.03]","Caption":"In this course we're going\r\nto go over the subject of\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:25.05]","Caption":"rigging a character in Blender,\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:27.03]","Caption":"starting with creating bones,\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:28.09]","Caption":"based on the location of our mesh.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:30.07]","Caption":"After that we'll discuss how to set up\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:32.07]","Caption":"inverse kineamtics to make\r\nthe feet stay on the ground\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:35.08]","Caption":"when you move the main part\r\nof the body for example.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:38.03]","Caption":"Next we'll look at how to add\r\ncontroller shapes to our bones\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:41.04]","Caption":"to make selecting them easier\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:43.02]","Caption":"and indicate the way\r\nthey're meant to be used.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:45.05]","Caption":"We'll then show you how to\r\nduplicate the left side bones\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:48.01]","Caption":"over to the right side to avoid needing to\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:49.07]","Caption":"create them from scratch.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:51.06]","Caption":"And finally, we'll show\r\nyou how to weight the mesh\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:53.08]","Caption":"to your rig and then tweak the weighting\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:55.07]","Caption":"until it moves exactly the\r\nway you would like it to.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:58.06]","Caption":"So let's go ahead and get started with\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:00.01]","Caption":"Rigging a Humanoid Character in Blender.\r\n\r\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:03.03]","Caption":""}]